description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Due to the changing face of healthcare within our Services extra funding has been secured for new roles and reconfiguration of some of our services.&lt;/strong&gt; This is an exciting challenge in the present climate and we need staff to support us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Want to help Leicestershire Partnership NHS Trust as a #NHSHero.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for Band 6 Charge Nurses (RGNs and RMNs) to join us across the Trust in Leicestershire to help support our Inpatient and Community Services and to help support with the Covid-19 situation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re flexible on hours that you’d like to work and can offer permanent contracts and bank/casual roles to work around your current commitments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested, please complete the application form and one of the team will be in touch to discuss further. If you’d like more information on the roles, please have a look at the attached Job Description.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As you can imagine, we’re currently recruiting in high volumes, so it may take the team a little longer than usual to get back to you but we do really appreciate your interest in coming to work for us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;See the link for benefits of working for LPT. Relocation may be available subject to our Trust policy criteria.&lt;/p&gt;
